CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1783952425
OL,3,CBritish woman becomes 13th person to
OL,4,Cdie in Spanish wildfires
OL,6,FAnother of the rescuers, Rafael Zea,
OL,7,Fsaid that given the couple's injuries,
OL,8,Fit must have taken a "Titanic effort"
OL,9,Ffor them to raise their voices to be
OL,10,Fheard.
OL,12,FWith the help of firefighters and
OL,13,Femergency services, they were rescued
OL,14,Fafter more than two hours.
OL,16,FThe pair are now said to be in a
OL,17,Fserious condition in hospital,
OL,18,Falthough their lives are not believed
OL,19,Fto be in danger.
OL,26,@pD@VOUpD@eO]
